    "plan_content": "Here's a summary of what I found and planned:\n\n---\n\n## What I Discovered\n\n**`AutoModelForImageTextToText` already exists** in `src/models.js` (line 8736) with mappings for 11 VLM architectures (LLaVA, SmolVLM, Qwen2-VL, PaliGemma, Moondream1, Florence2, Idefics3, etc.). It just has no pipeline in `src/pipelines.js`.\n\n**Only one file needs to change: `src/pipelines.js`**\n\n---\n\n## Implementation Plan (5 steps)\n\n1. **Add import** — `AutoModelForImageTextToText` to the `from './models.js'` import block\n\n2. **Add JSDoc typedefs** — `ImageTextToTextSingle`, `ImageTextToTextOutput`, `ImageTextToTextPipelineCallback`, `ImageTextToTextPipelineType` — after `ImageToTextPipeline` (line 2005)\n\n3. **Add `ImageTextToTextPipeline` class** with:\n   - `_call(text, images, generate_kwargs = {})` — **text first** to match modern VLM processors (Qwen2VL, Idefics3/SmolVLM)\n   - Calls `this.processor(text, preparedImages)` — the model-specific processor handles image-token expansion + tokenization together\n   - **Input prefix stripping**: decoder-only VLMs return `[input + generated]` from `generate()`. Mirrors `TextGenerationPipeline` (lines 1053–1058): decode `inputs.input_ids` → measure char length → slice from the full decoded output\n   - Returns `[{ generated_text }]` per input\n\n4. **Register in `SUPPORTED_TASKS`** after `\"image-to-text\"`, using `AutoModelForImageTextToText`, `AutoTokenizer`, `AutoProcessor`, type `\"multimodal\"`, default model `\"onnx-community/SmolVLM-Instruct\"`\n\n5. **Update `pipeline()` JSDoc** with `\"image-text-to-text\"` task entry in alphabetical order",
